primevc.types.Number

type
class
Defines the min and max values of integers

Static Variables

EMPTY(inline,null) : Int

Integer-value to indicate a value is set but doesn't have a value. If for example the height is set to 'none' in the css, it wil become NONE. This way the style-object won't look in other style-classes.

FLOAT_MAX(inline,null) : Float

FLOAT_NOT_SET(inline,null) : Float

INT_MAX(inline,null) : Int

INT_MIN(inline,null) : Int

INT_NOT_SET(inline,null) : Int

Value defining an undefined Int. Useful for AVM2 since there's no value like Math.NaN for integers..
